README.md

Awesome

   A curated list of assets availible on the Internet related to chess.

   Inspired by the [https://github.com/sindresorhus/awesome]awesome list
   thing. You might want to read the complete
   [https://github.com/sindresorhus/awesome]awesome list.

Contributing

   Kindly go through
   [https://github.com/hkirat/awesome-chess/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#co
   ntribution-guidelines]Contribution Guidelines first.

Content

     * Books
     * FEN Parsers
     * Move Validators
     * Bots
     * Websites
     * Boards
     * Board Notations
     * Pieces
     * Talks

Books

   Books to read on chess.
     * [https://kairavacademydotcom.files.wordpress.com/2013/06/john-thurs
       by-75-chess-problems.pdf]Chess Problems - Collection of chess
       puzzles.
     * [http://www.gutenberg.org/cache/epub/5614/pg5614-images.html]Chess
       strategy - HTML version of chess strategy by Edward Lasker.
     * [http://www.chesscity.com/PDF/Sicilian_Dragon_Black_Attacks_ssd.pdf
       ]Sicilian Dragon - Attacking plans for black.

FEN Parsers

   Forsyth-Edwards Notation (FEN) is a standard notation for describing a
   particular board position of a chess game.
     * [https://github.com/tlehman/fenparser]fenparser by tlehman - A
       parser for Forsyth-Edwards Notation wriitten in Python.
     * [https://github.com/ucarion/fen]fen by ucarion - A Rust
       Forsyth-Edwards notation parser with proper error handling.
     * [https://github.com/andyherbert/fen-diagram]fen-diagram by
       andyherbert - JavaScript for generating chess diagrams using
       Forsyth-Edwards notation.

Bots

   Bots are algorithms involving artificial intelligence to play against a
   user.
     * [https://github.com/benwr/latrunculorum]latrunculorum - A simple
       chess bot in Python.
     * [https://github.com/jfabeel/Chessbot]Chessbot - Bot written in
       Java.

Move Validators

   Validators are tools for checking authenticity of a move.
     * [https://github.com/jhlywa/chess.js]chess.js - chess.js, Structured
       code for chess authentication.
     * [https://www.npmjs.com/package/chess]npm chess package - An
       algebraic notation driven chess engine that can validate board
       position and produce a list of viable moves.
     * [https://github.com/cgearhart/Chessnut.git]Chessnut - Chessnut is a
       simple chess board model written in Python. It provides
       functionality of parsing FEN and generating a list of legal moves
       for each FEN representation.

Websites

   Websites include platforms for people to play chess.
     * [http://multiplayerchess.com/]multiplayerchess.com - A simple
       single page chess playing application facilitating the play of
       chess.
     * [http://en.lichess.org/]lichess.org - One of the most mature
       platforms for playing chess on the internet. It is open source too.
       It is equipped with daily puzzles and an TV to spectate other
       matches.
     * [https://chess24.com/en/play/chess]chess24.com - Play as well as
       learn chess from chess24 with the best of tutorials.
     * [http://play.chessbase.com/js/apps/playchess/]chessbase.com -
       Lucrative, single page application for playing chess.
     * [http://www.chess.com/]chess.com - Learn and play chess with over 5
       million other users.
     * [https://www.chesscademy.com/]chesscademy.com - Watch videos, solve
       puzzles, and play games. All for free. (Works similar to Khan
       Academy.)
     * [http://chesstempo.com/]chesstempo.com - Online chess tactics
       training site.
     * [https://chessprogramming.wikispaces.com/]chessprogramming.wikispac
       es.com - Repository of information about programming computers to
       play chess.
     * [http://freechess.org/]freechess.org - The 'Free Internet Chess
       Server' (FICS) is one of the oldest Internet chess servers. There
       are lots of client applications for almost every device, operation
       system or webbrowser available.

Boards

   Boards are tools for encapsulating the process of rendering a board.
     * [https://github.com/oakmac/chessboardjs/]Chessboard.js -
       chessboard.js is a standalone JavaScript chess board.
     * [https://github.com/laat/chess-board]chess-board - A web component
       for displaying chess positions. It takes FEN string as input and
       renders the board as output.
     * [https://github.com/bmarini/jchess]jchess - A jQuery based
       JavaScript library for parsing and displaying chess games.
       Currently takes FEN and PGN as inputs.
     * [https://github.com/caustique/chessboard-js]Chessboard-js - A
       responsive mobile-first JavaScript chessboard library.

Board Notations

   Notations are a way of expressing the properties of the board in
   textual format.
   [http://chess.eusa.ed.ac.uk/Chess/Rules/notation.html]Tutorial on Chess
   Notations.
     * [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Forsyth%E2%80%93Edwards_Notation]FEN
       - A FEN "record" defines a particular game position, all in one
       text line and using only the ASCII character set.
     * [http://www6.chessclub.com/help/PGN-spec]PNG - PGN is structured
       "for easy reading and writing by human users and for easy parsing
       and generation by computer programs."
     * Other Notations
          + [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Algebraic_notation_(chess)]Alge
            braic Chess Notation
          + [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ICCF_numeric_notation]ICCF
            numeric notation - Official chess game notation for all
            International Correspondence Chess Federation games.
          + [http://www6.chessclub.com/chessviewer/smith.html]Smith Chess
            Notation
          + [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Descriptive_notation]Descriptiv
            e Notation

Pieces

   This includes the tools for getting artwork for various pieces of
   chess.
     * [https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:470700]Spiral Pieces in 3-D
     * [https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:PNG_chess_pieces/Stand
       ard_transparent]Pieces on Wikipedia
     * [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chess_symbols_in_Unicode]Chess
       Pieces in Unicode
     * [http://www.flaticon.com/search/chess]Icons on flaticons
     * [https://thenounproject.com/search/?q=chess]Icons on thenounproject

Talks

   Talks on chess.
     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fPopQaY7Og4]Understanding Chess
       Mastery -Talk on understanding chess mastery by Jennifer Shahade.
     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A3yDvM8aplY]How Chess Can
       Revolutionize Learning - Talk on how chess can revolutionize
       learning by Cody Pomeranz.
     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v34NqCbAA1c]Working backward to
       solve problems - Talk on working backward to solve problems by
       Maurice Ashley
     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lgCSo1Txw3c]Chess Life
     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7EuxVOgrEig]Why Chess is Boring -
       Talk on why chess is boring by Bobby Fischer
     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p027ysBt0_M]Chess Peeps

